  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aim: to assess relative effectiveness of a high and a low intensity intervention for smoking
      cessation support in a dental clinic setting.

      Method: 300 smokers were randomly assigned to support with either low (LTI) or high treatment
      intensity (HTI).

      Main outcome measures were self-reported point-prevalence and continuous abstinence (≥183
      days).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
